}{}\begin{eqnarray*} {y_{ijkl}} &=& \mu + {\alpha _i} + {\beta _{ij}} + {\gamma _k} + {(\alpha \gamma )_{ik}}\nonumber\\ &&+\, {(\beta \gamma )_{ijk}} + {b_1} + {e_{ijkl}}, \end{eqnarray*}\end{document}Where: yijkl = lth observation of the ith diet type, jth diet, and kth inclusion level of enzymes, μ = general mean, αi = effect of the ith diet type, βij = effect of the jth diet within ith diet type, γk = effect of the kth inclusion level of enzymes, (αγ)jk = interaction effect between the ith diet type and kth inclusion level of enzymes, (βγ)ijk = interaction effect of the jth diet and the kth inclusion level of enzymes within the diet type, bl = effect of the lth incomplete block, and eijkl = error term associated with yijkl. Prior to statistical analyses, data were graphically checked for normal distribution and variance homogeneity, and if necessary (percentage data), subjected to arcsine square-root transformation. Least square means from the analysis were back-transformed for presentation only. If the F-test was significant, the multiple t test was used for treatment comparison. The level of significance was set at α = 0.05.
